Build Quaternion with Qt 5.3.

It builds and even runs but doesn't show avatars (QMetaObject::invokeMethod() tries to find QObject::requestAvatar() and fails); and it is unhappy about some GL symbols not found (don't ask me why) though it doesn't seem to break anything.
Fixed fetching avatars. Seems like it's fully functional with Qt 5.3 now.

Make Quaternion work with Qt 5.6

Qt 5.6 introduced 'HTTP redirects support' as they named it in What's new - thereby changing the default behaviour of QNetworkRequest: before 5.6 it used to follow redirects automatically, while in 5.6 you have to explicitly tell it to. Not sure if it's deliberate on their side - anyway, this commit makes use of the feature and fixes thumbnails loading that always goes through at least one redirect.

Introduce QDebug manipulators and formatJson manipulator in particular.

formatJson encapsulates QDebug::noquote() calls that don't exist on Qt 5.3 but are necessary since Qt 5.4 to remove excess quotes and accompanying escape sequences from QDebug outputs.

Also introduced logging_util.h - a collection of debug print utilities. So far consists of QDebug manipulators setup and check-and-log convenience function+macro.

Make sure avatarChanged signals are connected on fillup / cleanup of users in setRoom

Plus minor code cleanup.
Dropped unneeded check and debug message.
Deduplicate the code for connection and reconnection; connect the basejob completion signal before initiating the request, not after.

Non-functional changes: QList->QLinkedList, use std::algorithms to search an event insertion point.

1. Try to use QLinkedList for the timeline in the room (but not in MessageEventModel - it needs random-access).
2. Factor out the code that searches an event insertion point in the timeline, and rewrite it using std::lower_bound to (ok, marginally, nobody will notice) speed up insertion.
Replaced private one-line slots with lambdas.

Implemented room names and user names according to the CS spec.

1. User names are now disambiguated in the context of a specific room.
To avoid quadratic complexity, that required converting a flat list of
users in Room to a hashmap of members' displayNames to user object
pointers and changing all access to that list.
2. Room names are generated (according to the CS spec) out of
displayname, canonicalAlias, and member names (current, and then left).
Because of relying on member names, a room display name is now revised
every time the userlist of a room changes.

Dock widgets features restrained.

1. Remove Close button from the dock widgets - one cannot open them atm
if accidentally closed.
2. Only allow to stack the widgets to the left and right from the chat,
not on top or below.
